description:
&lt;p&gt;The position of Associate Lecturer within the Social Care, Leadership and Management portfolio has been introduced to enable greater capacity for doctoral supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These two posts comprise of 4 sessions (3.75hours) each in the Social Care, Leadership and Management Portfolio and are focussed on working on the professional doctorate programme in advanced practice and research: consultation and the organisation, D10D. It is a Professional doctorate and also part of the Trust’s Integrated Professional Doctorate programme (IPD) and validated by University of Essex. The post holder will provide supervision, tutoring, workshops and lecturing as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holders will be expected to offer availability throughout the annual academic cycle, but with the likelihood of more engagement during academic terms and less in holiday periods. They may also be involved in both recruitment and assessment processes and will assist flexibly in all aspects of courses delivery within the Portfolio and other portfolios where relevant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holders will be effective supervisors with a working knowledge of psychodynamic and/or systemic theories, interventions and approaches to research. They will offer high quality supervisory experiences supporting the Trust’s reputation as a leader in education and training in health and social care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust is a National Health Service post-graduate training institution and is also a resource for consultation to professionals in other centres and in the community, within both the public and voluntary sectors, covering health, social services and education. The overall major concern is with the prevention of mental illness and he promotion of mental health, and its research work is in support of these aims. In all aspects of its work the Trust is committed to the development of anti-discriminatory practice and the provision of equal opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The social care, leadership and management portfolio comprises a range of post graduate courses in Social work and Social Care, Consulting and Leading in Organisations as well as a range of CPD courses. The portfolio is made up of a small, dedicated staff group who teach across these programmes as well as engage in the development of new provision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates are requested to use the section &quot;Supporting Information&quot; on the application form to set out their reasons for applying and their suitability, referring to the person specification, for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
